    <section>
        <h2>Body</h2>
        <p>As I got older, I started doing more sports, especially football. Primary and secondary changed my life because I learned new things, made friends, and grew as a person.</p>
        <p>Before school, I was more playful and less focused. Now I am more serious about my goals and hobbies.</p>
        <p>Things I didn’t like when I was younger: reading and writing. Now I like working hard, playing sports, and learning new things.</p>
        <p>Currently, I enjoy football and setting goals. My hobbies now include sports and learning about business. I dislike wasting time or giving up easily.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Fun Facts</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Funny: I once screamed in a snow park because I got scared of a snowman.</li>
            <li>Bad: I once lost my football shoes before a big game.</li>
            <li>Good: I won a football tournament when I was 6.</li>
            <li>Proud: I’m proud of my improvement in school and sports.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Final</h2>
        <p>In the future, I want to go to high school for one year in Canada at BCS. After that, I want to study business in Mexico and live in Switzerland.</p>
        <p>Some of my goals are to have my own company and to travel around the world. I already achieved many small goals, like becoming better at football and being more disciplined.</p>
        <p>I believe in working hard, having clear goals, and always thinking like a winner.</p>
    </section>

